==English==
===Intransitive Verb===
'''to halt'''
# to [[stop]] either [[temporarily]] or [[permanently]]
# to cause something to stop
#* ''The contract negotiations '''halted''' operations for at least a week.''
# to waver or be hesitant

===Noun===
'''halt'''
# a [[cessation]] either [[temporary]] or [[permanent]]
#* ''The contract negotiations put a '''halt''' on operations.

===Interjection===
'''Halt!'''
# [[Stop]]!
##''Usage'':  Military squad leaders use '''halt''' as a command to stop troops that are moving in formation.  Also used in command to persons about to enter a guarded area, or to stop a fleeing enemy or prisoner.